This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel method for time-series classification using shapelets, which is a popular technique in machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of supervised shapelet selection, which is a common approach in machine learning. 

The paper could also belong to the data mining (cs.DM) sub-category as time-series classification is an important problem in data mining, and the proposed method involves discovering patterns in time-series data. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a method for improving the prediction accuracy of time-series classification, which is a common task in artificial intelligence. 

Computer vision (cs.CV) could also be a relevant sub-category as the proposed method involves discovering patterns in time-series data, which is a common task in computer vision. 

Finally, the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of shapelets for time-series classification, which is a common task in information retrieval.
